                <hr>

                <h2>Responsive method - using Pym.js</h2>
                <p>Using iframes in a responsive page can be more difficult as sizing its height is tricky â€” especially if the content of the iframe changes height depending on page width (for example, because of text wrapping or media queries) or events within the iframe. To get round this we normally use <a href = "http://blog.apps.npr.org/pym.js/">Pym.js</a>.</p>
                <p>To embed a chart using pym you will need the following in your page (amending the chart name and URL as appropriate);
                <pre><code class="language-markup">
&#x3C;div id=&#x22;chart1&#x22;&#x3E;&#x3C;/div&#x3E;
